The paper deals with the problem of decoding signals transmitted over an asynchronous multiple-access channel (MAC) with arbitrary pulse-shaping. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of Low-Density Parity-Check (LDPC) codes and physical-layer network coding, which are common topics in coding theory (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of cyclic codes for combating frame-asynchronism, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
